<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-11T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/677: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Southgate</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-11T17:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">April 11,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 12—9:30
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. General amnesty has been decreed. All political prisoners except
                            those actually engaged in acts of violence have been released.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Southgate</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>